subject: Re: [junit] JunitReport
msgSnippet: ... Probably a WebLogic .jar file. Try adding them all, then taking ones away until you see the problem again, then you know which one you need. -- J. B. (Joe)
messageBody:
arro9999 wrote:
>
>
> When I run junitreport from ant it throws the exception
>
> "couldnt find a valid processor version implementation from
> weblogic.xml.jaxp.RegistrySAXTransformerFactory"
>
> Please let me know what am i missing here,

Probably a WebLogic .jar file. Try adding them all, then taking ones
away until you see the problem again, then you know which one you need.
--
